00:28:43.980 --> 00:28:47.015 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Will the people
win in the long run?

00:28:47.015 --> 00:28:48.060 align:middle line:90%
It's a tough call, Pat.

00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:50.720 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: This is the question,
because by and large,

00:28:50.720 --> 00:28:52.260 align:middle line:84%
the people still
don't understand.

00:28:52.260 --> 00:28:56.280 align:middle line:84%
But when it gets into
their pocketbook,

00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:59.220 align:middle line:84%
and they start to feel the
noose around their neck,

00:28:59.220 --> 00:29:02.520 align:middle line:84%
that's when they start
kicking back and resisting.

00:29:02.520 --> 00:29:04.720 align:middle line:84%
The fact that anybody is
resisting is a good thing,

00:29:04.720 --> 00:29:05.520 align:middle line:90%
I think.

00:29:05.520 --> 00:29:06.615 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: As long as nobody dies.

00:29:06.615 --> 00:29:08.040 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: As long as nobody dies.

00:29:08.040 --> 00:29:09.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that
could be the next step.

00:29:09.780 --> 00:29:11.350 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That's the problem.

00:29:11.350 --> 00:29:14.880 align:middle line:84%
We don't-- heaven forbid that we
would have a civil war in this

00:29:14.880 --> 00:29:16.890 align:middle line:84%
country, or anywhere
else, for that matter,

00:29:16.890 --> 00:29:19.360 align:middle line:90%
then more people would die.

00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:21.360 align:middle line:84%
You know, we can complain
about war all we want,

00:29:21.360 --> 00:29:22.620 align:middle line:84%
it's not going to
do away with war.

00:29:22.620 --> 00:29:23.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:29:23.640 --> 00:29:25.170 align:middle line:90%
What are smart cities?

00:29:25.170 --> 00:29:26.910 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Smart city,
by definition,

00:29:26.910 --> 00:29:28.620 align:middle line:84%
is the application
of quote, unquote,

00:29:28.620 --> 00:29:33.610 align:middle line:84%
smart technology on top
of society, within a city.

00:29:33.610 --> 00:29:35.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It appears
great, doesn't it?

00:29:35.430 --> 00:29:36.875 align:middle line:90%
It makes you think it's good.

00:29:36.875 --> 00:29:39.000 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Well, it's like
the United Nations promises

00:29:39.000 --> 00:29:40.260 align:middle line:90%
to end poverty.

00:29:40.260 --> 00:29:43.070 align:middle line:84%
They have jobs for
everyone, with dignity.

00:29:43.070 --> 00:29:44.820 align:middle line:84%
They have lifelong
learning opportunities.

00:29:44.820 --> 00:29:45.990 align:middle line:90%
You see that kind of rhetoric.

00:29:45.990 --> 00:29:47.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Medical
help for the world.

00:29:47.070 --> 00:29:48.528 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Medical
help for the world.

00:29:48.528 --> 00:29:50.310 align:middle line:90%
It's promise of utopia.

00:29:50.310 --> 00:29:51.690 align:middle line:90%
Can they deliver utopia?

00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:53.110 align:middle line:90%
No, they can't.

00:29:53.110 --> 00:29:55.860 align:middle line:84%
They've never been
able to deliver utopia.

00:29:55.860 --> 00:29:58.800 align:middle line:84%
But the idea of
smart cities today

00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:03.180 align:middle line:84%
is to take advanced
technology and turn the city

00:30:03.180 --> 00:30:07.260 align:middle line:84%
into a living laboratory
that could be managed--

00:30:07.260 --> 00:30:10.030 align:middle line:84%
again, by algorithm, by
artificial intelligence,

00:30:10.030 --> 00:30:12.480 align:middle line:84%
that could be managed by the
people that run the city.

00:30:12.480 --> 00:30:14.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now when you deal
with smart technology,

00:30:14.670 --> 00:30:16.590 align:middle line:84%
we're dealing with
what specifically?

00:30:16.590 --> 00:30:20.490 align:middle line:84%
Somebody in some computer room
somewhere, running lights?

00:30:20.490 --> 00:30:22.500 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Let me give
an example in China.

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:27.040 align:middle line:84%
China, now, has said, by 2020--
that's two years from now--

00:30:27.040 --> 00:30:31.920 align:middle line:84%
they will have installed 600
million facial recognition

00:30:31.920 --> 00:30:32.720 align:middle line:90%
cameras--

00:30:32.720 --> 00:30:33.880 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes, everywhere.

00:30:33.880 --> 00:30:34.870 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: --throughout
the country.

00:30:34.870 --> 00:30:35.810 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Everywhere.

00:30:35.810 --> 00:30:39.820 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: This is a country
that has 1.4 billion people.

00:30:39.820 --> 00:30:42.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So almost a camera
for every two people.

00:30:42.010 --> 00:30:45.070 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: That's one camera
for every 2 and 1/2 people.

00:30:45.070 --> 00:30:48.520 align:middle line:84%
They could find you, from
the time the order is put out

00:30:48.520 --> 00:30:51.280 align:middle line:84%
to say, find George Noory,
we want George Noory in here

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:53.020 align:middle line:90%
to ask him some questions.

00:30:53.020 --> 00:30:55.380 align:middle line:84%
That usually is not
a good thing, right?

00:30:55.380 --> 00:30:56.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Not there.

00:30:56.270 --> 00:30:57.500 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Not there.

00:30:57.500 --> 00:31:00.430 align:middle line:84%
But when they push the
button to find George Noory,

00:31:00.430 --> 00:31:03.520 align:middle line:84%
they can find you, they say,
within two to three minutes.

00:31:03.520 --> 00:31:04.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:31:04.330 --> 00:31:05.710 align:middle line:84%
They put my face
into the system?

00:31:05.710 --> 00:31:06.510 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Yes.

00:31:06.510 --> 00:31:08.093 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And then
the camera finds me.

00:31:08.093 --> 00:31:09.010 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That's right.

00:31:09.010 --> 00:31:11.075 align:middle line:84%
The cameras will identify
you around the country.

00:31:11.075 --> 00:31:11.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: There he is.

00:31:11.950 --> 00:31:13.985 align:middle line:84%
He walked into his
apartment or his house.

00:31:13.985 --> 00:31:14.860 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That's right.

00:31:14.860 --> 00:31:19.950 align:middle line:84%
So this kind of
complete surveillance

00:31:19.950 --> 00:31:22.620 align:middle line:90%
is a system of control.

00:31:22.620 --> 00:31:25.990 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't just stop
there with cameras and China.

00:31:25.990 --> 00:31:30.310 align:middle line:84%
They now have this social
credit scoring system,

00:31:30.310 --> 00:31:32.320 align:middle line:84%
where they're assigning
scores to people

00:31:32.320 --> 00:31:36.747 align:middle line:84%
based on how good a citizen
you are to the state.

00:31:36.747 --> 00:31:38.080 align:middle line:90%
See, this is social engineering.

00:31:38.080 --> 00:31:39.538 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As long
as you keep quiet,

00:31:39.538 --> 00:31:40.871 align:middle line:90%
you'll have a nice credit score.

00:31:40.871 --> 00:31:41.671 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Well, yeah.

00:31:41.671 --> 00:31:42.713 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Raise a little--

00:31:42.713 --> 00:31:44.380 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: If you're
friendly to the state,

00:31:44.380 --> 00:31:47.967 align:middle line:84%
and we can count on you to
always say, yes, sir, yes,

00:31:47.967 --> 00:31:49.300 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We'll take care of you.

00:31:49.300 --> 00:31:50.350 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That's right.

00:31:50.350 --> 00:31:51.940 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:31:51.940 --> 00:31:53.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: If you rock the boat--

00:31:53.710 --> 00:31:56.890 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Well you may not even
politically rock the boat.

00:31:56.890 --> 00:31:59.710 align:middle line:84%
But let's say you have
a habit of jaywalking,

00:31:59.710 --> 00:32:02.200 align:middle line:84%
or you don't pay
your bills on time,

00:32:02.200 --> 00:32:04.930 align:middle line:84%
or you got divorced
once or something.

00:32:04.930 --> 00:32:06.670 align:middle line:84%
All these things can
weigh against you.

00:32:06.670 --> 00:32:08.212 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They'll
have a point system.

00:32:08.212 --> 00:32:10.810 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: The point system
is all done by computer.

00:32:10.810 --> 00:32:14.370 align:middle line:84%
There's not a man sitting there
figuring out that you and I are

00:32:14.370 --> 00:32:15.800 align:middle line:90%
going to get a score.

00:32:15.800 --> 00:32:17.680 align:middle line:84%
It's all done by
computer, by algorithm.

00:32:17.680 --> 00:32:18.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You can't buy a car--

00:32:18.190 --> 00:32:19.075 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Artificial intelligence.

00:32:19.075 --> 00:32:20.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --because
of your score,

00:32:20.450 --> 00:32:22.450 align:middle line:84%
you can't do this
because of your score.

00:32:22.450 --> 00:32:25.297 align:middle line:84%
You may not get hired
because of your score.

00:32:25.297 --> 00:32:27.130 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Not only that,
you might not travel.

00:32:27.130 --> 00:32:29.422 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you can't buy a plane
ticket or a train ticket.

00:32:29.422 --> 00:32:30.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Talking
about travel, I've

00:32:30.880 --> 00:32:32.660 align:middle line:90%
been to Toronto several times.

00:32:32.660 --> 00:32:33.850 align:middle line:90%
It's a gorgeous city.

00:32:33.850 --> 00:32:38.502 align:middle line:84%
Microsoft wants to turn
Toronto into a smart city.

00:32:38.502 --> 00:32:40.210 align:middle line:10%
>>NARRATOR: Smart
cities are about making

00:32:40.210 --> 00:32:42.220 align:middle line:10%
each individual part
of a city smarter

00:32:42.220 --> 00:32:44.830 align:middle line:10%
through sensors,
infrastructure, and AI,

00:32:44.830 --> 00:32:47.050 align:middle line:10%
then connecting them
altogether through the cloud

00:32:47.050 --> 00:32:48.970 align:middle line:10%
to operate seamlessly together.

00:32:48.970 --> 00:32:51.220 align:middle line:10%
>>CAMERON CARR: Once we do
that, we can solve problems

00:32:51.220 --> 00:32:54.977 align:middle line:10%
before they start, which is
really the end goal here.

00:32:54.977 --> 00:32:56.560 align:middle line:10%
>>ERIKA BASHAM: There
really is no end

00:32:56.560 --> 00:32:59.440 align:middle line:10%
to what could be enabled
with a smart city.

00:32:59.440 --> 00:33:01.630 align:middle line:10%
It's all connected
together to operate

00:33:01.630 --> 00:33:04.510 align:middle line:10%
as one cohesive unit
aimed at improving

00:33:04.510 --> 00:33:07.127 align:middle line:10%
the lives of the
citizens of the city.

00:33:07.127 --> 00:33:09.460 align:middle line:10%
>>PHIL KORETZ: So you put
sensors in your traffic lights

00:33:09.460 --> 00:33:12.140 align:middle line:10%
to help to optimize route
times and decrease congestion

00:33:12.140 --> 00:33:13.150 align:middle line:10%
at given hours.

00:33:13.150 --> 00:33:16.000 align:middle line:10%
Route optimization for your
trucks for waste disposal.

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:19.020 align:middle line:10%
For water, you can use sensors
to measure water quality

00:33:19.020 --> 00:33:19.990 align:middle line:10%
and flow.

00:33:19.990 --> 00:33:22.240 align:middle line:10%
All of these different
technologies taken together

00:33:22.240 --> 00:33:24.730 align:middle line:10%
make for a better experience
for you as a citizen,

00:33:24.730 --> 00:33:26.200 align:middle line:10%
and make the city
government better

00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:27.838 align:middle line:10%
able to accomplish their goals.

00:33:27.838 --> 00:33:31.120 align:middle line:90%


00:33:31.120 --> 00:33:33.190 align:middle line:10%
>>MIKELE BRACK: Uplift
is an urban pilot

00:33:33.190 --> 00:33:37.140 align:middle line:10%
program that was developed
by Urban Living Futures.

00:33:37.140 --> 00:33:40.440 align:middle line:10%
There are three major
elements to those programs.

00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:44.400 align:middle line:10%
There are the cities and the
companies within those cities

00:33:44.400 --> 00:33:47.490 align:middle line:10%
that have challenges or
aspirations around technology

00:33:47.490 --> 00:33:50.520 align:middle line:10%
that innovators can
help them to address.

00:33:50.520 --> 00:33:53.190 align:middle line:10%
>>CHERYL GRAY: I think
the introduction of IoT,

00:33:53.190 --> 00:33:56.790 align:middle line:10%
it really is around trying to
create an environment where

00:33:56.790 --> 00:33:59.760 align:middle line:10%
not only our
occupants, our tenants,

00:33:59.760 --> 00:34:05.790 align:middle line:10%
our residents have an experience
that is far easier and far more

00:34:05.790 --> 00:34:09.719 align:middle line:10%
meaningful in ways that I think
we can't really even envision

00:34:09.719 --> 00:34:11.130 align:middle line:10%
today.

00:34:11.130 --> 00:34:13.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now it sounds
exciting, but in the hands

00:34:13.620 --> 00:34:18.360 align:middle line:84%
of the wrong people, who knows
what they could do with this.

00:34:18.360 --> 00:34:19.969 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: That's
exactly the point.

00:34:19.969 --> 00:34:24.960 align:middle line:84%
And privacy is completely
dissolved in a smart city.

00:34:24.960 --> 00:34:25.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Gone.

00:34:25.760 --> 00:34:27.000 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Just gone.

00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:29.272 align:middle line:84%
They will know more
about you probably

00:34:29.272 --> 00:34:30.480 align:middle line:90%
than you know about yourself.

00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:31.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's true.

00:34:31.800 --> 00:34:34.350 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: And they can use that
information to control you.

00:34:34.350 --> 00:34:35.460 align:middle line:90%
That's the problem.

00:34:35.460 --> 00:34:38.870 align:middle line:84%
That's where the resistance
kickback is coming.

00:34:38.870 --> 00:34:44.909 align:middle line:84%
In Toronto, in particular,
the Microsoft and Google

00:34:44.909 --> 00:34:50.780 align:middle line:84%
project up there to create
a smart city has encountered

00:34:50.780 --> 00:34:53.000 align:middle line:84%
incredible problems
with people--

00:34:53.000 --> 00:34:53.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Already?

00:34:53.840 --> 00:34:56.500 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: --already that are
fighting back against it,

00:34:56.500 --> 00:34:58.520 align:middle line:84%
on all kinds of
different levels that you

00:34:58.520 --> 00:35:01.130 align:middle line:90%
wouldn't expect, necessarily.

00:35:01.130 --> 00:35:04.380 align:middle line:84%
But see, the problem is,
these smart city designers,

00:35:04.380 --> 00:35:06.290 align:middle line:90%
where does this stuff come from?

00:35:06.290 --> 00:35:09.340 align:middle line:84%
Are these your city council
people that come up with this?

00:35:09.340 --> 00:35:10.370 align:middle line:90%
you're mayor?

00:35:10.370 --> 00:35:11.900 align:middle line:90%
city manager?

00:35:11.900 --> 00:35:13.670 align:middle line:90%
No, it's big data.

00:35:13.670 --> 00:35:15.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Even those
workers we just saw,

00:35:15.530 --> 00:35:18.600 align:middle line:84%
Pat, seem well-intentioned,
those people.

00:35:18.600 --> 00:35:20.100 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: But they
work for Microsoft,

00:35:20.100 --> 00:35:22.220 align:middle line:84%
they work for Amazon,
they work for Google,

00:35:22.220 --> 00:35:24.680 align:middle line:84%
they work for these
big tech companies--

00:35:24.680 --> 00:35:26.060 align:middle line:90%
Microsoft and whatever.

00:35:26.060 --> 00:35:29.600 align:middle line:84%
These are not elected
representatives of the people,

00:35:29.600 --> 00:35:33.350 align:middle line:84%
nor do they consult the
people on what people want

00:35:33.350 --> 00:35:35.180 align:middle line:90%
to do in their particular city.

00:35:35.180 --> 00:35:37.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What will
happen 20 years from now

00:35:37.370 --> 00:35:39.620 align:middle line:90%
if all this is implemented?

00:35:39.620 --> 00:35:41.390 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Much of it
is going to fail.

00:35:41.390 --> 00:35:43.610 align:middle line:90%
I'll say that right up front.

00:35:43.610 --> 00:35:46.100 align:middle line:84%
The whole concept of
public-private partnerships,

00:35:46.100 --> 00:35:50.860 align:middle line:84%
where you have a public entity
like Toronto combining together

00:35:50.860 --> 00:35:55.130 align:middle line:84%
with a private entity, whether
it be Google or Microsoft,

00:35:55.130 --> 00:35:58.190 align:middle line:84%
this is kind of a fascist
type of a blending, of state

00:35:58.190 --> 00:36:00.750 align:middle line:90%
into business.

00:36:00.750 --> 00:36:04.630 align:middle line:84%
When the business partnership
goes south, George,

00:36:04.630 --> 00:36:06.372 align:middle line:90%
the people can't leave.

00:36:06.372 --> 00:36:07.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They're stuck.

00:36:07.330 --> 00:36:08.500 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: They're stuck.

00:36:08.500 --> 00:36:11.830 align:middle line:84%
The corporations can waltz
away and go find somebody else

00:36:11.830 --> 00:36:13.630 align:middle line:90%
to take advantage.

00:36:13.630 --> 00:36:16.390 align:middle line:90%
They leave the city with hubris.

00:36:16.390 --> 00:36:21.310 align:middle line:84%
This has happened all over the
planet with these companies--

00:36:21.310 --> 00:36:23.900 align:middle line:84%
with these large
companies that do this.

00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:25.540 align:middle line:84%
There are so many
examples that just

00:36:25.540 --> 00:36:27.250 align:middle line:90%
make your hair stand on end.

00:36:27.250 --> 00:36:30.100 align:middle line:84%
But this is basically-- the
whole concept of smart city

00:36:30.100 --> 00:36:33.430 align:middle line:84%
is, we're going to come
in and save the day.

00:36:33.430 --> 00:36:35.830 align:middle line:84%
We're going to create this
great new thing that's

00:36:35.830 --> 00:36:39.010 align:middle line:84%
never been tested
before, never been tried.

00:36:39.010 --> 00:36:41.740 align:middle line:84%
We don't know if the people
are going to like it at all.

00:36:41.740 --> 00:36:44.530 align:middle line:84%
We don't know if it's
going to be successful.

00:36:44.530 --> 00:36:47.890 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to come in a
turn your world upside down.

00:36:47.890 --> 00:36:49.340 align:middle line:90%
We hope it's going to work.

00:36:49.340 --> 00:36:52.008 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What would George
Orwell have said about today?

00:36:52.008 --> 00:36:53.800 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: He would say
this is the end result

00:36:53.800 --> 00:36:55.517 align:middle line:90%
of a scientific dictatorship.

00:36:55.517 --> 00:36:57.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, he
was right about '84.

00:36:57.100 --> 00:36:58.000 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: He was right.

00:36:58.000 --> 00:36:59.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Maybe he was early.

00:36:59.710 --> 00:37:03.240 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Orwell
understood technocracy.

00:37:03.240 --> 00:37:05.550 align:middle line:90%
So did Huxley.

00:37:05.550 --> 00:37:07.410 align:middle line:10%
Huxley, by the way,
wrote his book,

00:37:07.410 --> 00:37:10.580 align:middle line:10%
"Brave New World," in 1932.

00:37:10.580 --> 00:37:12.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Way before technology.

00:37:12.270 --> 00:37:15.840 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Well, you'll
remember that 1932

00:37:15.840 --> 00:37:20.880 align:middle line:84%
was the year that technocracy
was at Columbia University.

00:37:20.880 --> 00:37:24.570 align:middle line:84%
And Huxley, a Brit,
had a connection

00:37:24.570 --> 00:37:28.007 align:middle line:84%
to the president of
Columbia University.

00:37:28.007 --> 00:37:29.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And he knew
about this, then.

00:37:29.590 --> 00:37:31.150 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Absolutely.

00:37:31.150 --> 00:37:34.400 align:middle line:84%
So scientific dictatorship
has not been-- it's

00:37:34.400 --> 00:37:36.410 align:middle line:90%
not a new concept.

00:37:36.410 --> 00:37:38.830 align:middle line:84%
But you go back and you read
some of the futuristic stuff

00:37:38.830 --> 00:37:40.990 align:middle line:84%
that Huxley wrote,
and you think, man,

00:37:40.990 --> 00:37:42.880 align:middle line:84%
how did this guy come
up with this stuff?

00:37:42.880 --> 00:37:45.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Pat, what
are they afraid of?

00:37:45.340 --> 00:37:49.300 align:middle line:84%
When I say "they,"
it's that big umbrella.

00:37:49.300 --> 00:37:51.130 align:middle line:84%
What are they afraid
of with the people?

00:37:51.130 --> 00:37:53.230 align:middle line:90%
Why did they want this control?

00:37:53.230 --> 00:37:55.240 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: They're afraid
of you and me, George.

00:37:55.240 --> 00:37:57.260 align:middle line:90%
They're afraid of people.

00:37:57.260 --> 00:38:02.390 align:middle line:84%
Most of this crowd has
never had any direct contact

00:38:02.390 --> 00:38:06.920 align:middle line:84%
with real people that
live in real cities

00:38:06.920 --> 00:38:09.560 align:middle line:90%
and real communities.

00:38:09.560 --> 00:38:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And when they're confronted
by people who take exception--

00:38:14.980 --> 00:38:19.030 align:middle line:84%
and I have confronted many
over the last 40 years.

00:38:19.030 --> 00:38:21.560 align:middle line:84%
When they're
confronted, they go,

00:38:21.560 --> 00:38:24.210 align:middle line:90%
I can't believe you're upset.

00:38:24.210 --> 00:38:26.738 align:middle line:84%
I don't know-- what
are you thinking?

00:38:26.738 --> 00:38:29.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, they think
they are developing a utopia.

00:38:29.030 --> 00:38:29.830 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Yeah.

00:38:29.830 --> 00:38:32.730 align:middle line:84%
They think, well,
of course it's good.

00:38:32.730 --> 00:38:35.380 align:middle line:90%
Why would you protest?

00:38:35.380 --> 00:38:36.880 align:middle line:84%
And for the most
part, most of them

00:38:36.880 --> 00:38:39.490 align:middle line:84%
are like deer caught
in the headlights.

00:38:39.490 --> 00:38:42.550 align:middle line:84%
They just can't believe
that anybody would not

00:38:42.550 --> 00:38:44.347 align:middle line:90%
go along with the program.

00:38:44.347 --> 00:38:46.180 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've never
quite figured this out,

00:38:46.180 --> 00:38:48.670 align:middle line:90%
but I've seen it so many times.

00:38:48.670 --> 00:38:51.820 align:middle line:84%
Back in the early writings
of technocracy, in the '30s,

00:38:51.820 --> 00:38:54.640 align:middle line:84%
they wanted to convert North
America into a technate,

00:38:54.640 --> 00:38:55.960 align:middle line:90%
they called it.

00:38:55.960 --> 00:38:57.460 align:middle line:90%
It was going to be Canada--

00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:58.630 align:middle line:90%
they had a map.

00:38:58.630 --> 00:39:03.700 align:middle line:84%
Canada, United States, Mexico,
all the Central America,

00:39:03.700 --> 00:39:07.540 align:middle line:84%
and most of the northern
part of South America.

00:39:07.540 --> 00:39:12.080 align:middle line:84%
That was the technate that they
were going to put all together.

00:39:12.080 --> 00:39:14.140 align:middle line:84%
There's not one word
I could find anywhere

00:39:14.140 --> 00:39:17.780 align:middle line:84%
and their original
information that

00:39:17.780 --> 00:39:20.030 align:middle line:84%
said how they were going to
talk these other countries

00:39:20.030 --> 00:39:22.242 align:middle line:90%
into doing it.

00:39:22.242 --> 00:39:24.200 align:middle line:84%
What, Canada's just going
to roll over and play

00:39:24.200 --> 00:39:26.720 align:middle line:84%
dead, and say, hey sure,
we'll join your technate.

00:39:26.720 --> 00:39:28.040 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right-- or Mexico.

00:39:28.040 --> 00:39:28.890 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Mexico.

00:39:28.890 --> 00:39:29.780 align:middle line:90%
Are you kidding?

00:39:29.780 --> 00:39:31.400 align:middle line:90%
South America?

00:39:31.400 --> 00:39:36.230 align:middle line:84%
I mean, are we going to go in
and conquer them militarily?

00:39:36.230 --> 00:39:37.550 align:middle line:90%
But they never brought that up.

00:39:37.550 --> 00:39:39.740 align:middle line:90%
They never talked about that.

00:39:39.740 --> 00:39:43.550 align:middle line:84%
This is the problem
with Pollyanna dreamers.

00:39:43.550 --> 00:39:45.710 align:middle line:90%
They don't think things through.

00:39:45.710 --> 00:39:47.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you mentioned
one of the goals.

00:39:47.960 --> 00:39:50.950 align:middle line:90%
The main goal is resources.

00:39:50.950 --> 00:39:52.660 align:middle line:84%
Is there another goal,
though, behind it

00:39:52.660 --> 00:39:53.800 align:middle line:90%
with these individuals?

00:39:53.800 --> 00:39:56.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they put their
pants on like we do.

00:39:56.140 --> 00:39:59.740 align:middle line:90%
They cry, they eat, they sleep.

00:39:59.740 --> 00:40:01.360 align:middle line:90%
What's their end game?

00:40:01.360 --> 00:40:04.060 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: You could kind of
guess from it, the end game,

00:40:04.060 --> 00:40:06.250 align:middle line:84%
you could say, is
control and power.

00:40:06.250 --> 00:40:07.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They're
bored, aren't they?

00:40:07.750 --> 00:40:09.790 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: But the power
comes through the control

00:40:09.790 --> 00:40:11.230 align:middle line:90%
of the resources.

00:40:11.230 --> 00:40:13.990 align:middle line:84%
This has always been the
case on Planet Earth.

00:40:13.990 --> 00:40:16.840 align:middle line:84%
You know, you go back
to Old Testament days

00:40:16.840 --> 00:40:19.450 align:middle line:84%
when Job was alive,
for instance.

00:40:19.450 --> 00:40:23.300 align:middle line:84%
Job was one of the richest
men, if not the richest man,

00:40:23.300 --> 00:40:24.100 align:middle line:90%
on Earth.

00:40:24.100 --> 00:40:25.150 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:40:25.150 --> 00:40:28.660 align:middle line:84%
Well, he had sheep, he
had cattle, he had herds,

00:40:28.660 --> 00:40:30.070 align:middle line:90%
he had land, he had mines.

00:40:30.070 --> 00:40:31.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He had
thousands of them.

00:40:31.570 --> 00:40:33.730 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Thousands of them.

00:40:33.730 --> 00:40:36.400 align:middle line:90%
And he was a rich man.

00:40:36.400 --> 00:40:38.700 align:middle line:84%
He didn't have the Federal
Reserve in his back pocket

00:40:38.700 --> 00:40:39.500 align:middle line:90%
back then.

00:40:39.500 --> 00:40:41.350 align:middle line:90%
Just he had the resources.

00:40:41.350 --> 00:40:43.795 align:middle line:84%
That's always been
the measure of wealth.

00:40:43.795 --> 00:40:46.540 align:middle line:90%


00:40:46.540 --> 00:40:48.940 align:middle line:84%
The global elite that
wanted to get all the money

00:40:48.940 --> 00:40:51.320 align:middle line:84%
in the world-- like through
the Federal Reserve,

00:40:51.320 --> 00:40:54.050 align:middle line:84%
and chiseling off with
inflation, and so on--

00:40:54.050 --> 00:40:55.810 align:middle line:90%
they've had success with that.

00:40:55.810 --> 00:40:57.130 align:middle line:90%
Let's be frank.

00:40:57.130 --> 00:41:01.330 align:middle line:84%
They've chiseled away about
99% of the value of the dollar

00:41:01.330 --> 00:41:04.930 align:middle line:84%
since 1913, when
the Fed was created.

00:41:04.930 --> 00:41:06.910 align:middle line:90%
What's left to rip off?

00:41:06.910 --> 00:41:08.410 align:middle line:90%
Not much.

00:41:08.410 --> 00:41:10.210 align:middle line:84%
At this point, the
only thing left

00:41:10.210 --> 00:41:12.910 align:middle line:84%
to go for are the
resources of the planet.

00:41:12.910 --> 00:41:15.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How could
this backfire on them?

00:41:15.970 --> 00:41:18.140 align:middle line:90%
What could go wrong for them?

00:41:18.140 --> 00:41:21.580 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Well, when, as,
and if people figure out

00:41:21.580 --> 00:41:23.560 align:middle line:90%
the magician's trick here--

00:41:23.560 --> 00:41:28.360 align:middle line:84%
the fraud, if you will,
it could be game over.

00:41:28.360 --> 00:41:31.480 align:middle line:84%
But that's a big if,
because most people

00:41:31.480 --> 00:41:35.225 align:middle line:84%
still just absolutely don't
understand what's going on.

00:41:35.225 --> 00:41:36.850 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they
may never understand.

00:41:36.850 --> 00:41:38.433 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: And they may
never understand.

00:41:38.433 --> 00:41:41.560 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand, how
much do you need to know?

00:41:41.560 --> 00:41:44.260 align:middle line:84%
In France, for instance,
the yellow vests

00:41:44.260 --> 00:41:48.550 align:middle line:84%
are upset because they
don't like the carbon tax.

00:41:48.550 --> 00:41:50.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, the carbon tax
is directly related

00:41:50.530 --> 00:41:52.060 align:middle line:90%
to what we're talking about.

00:41:52.060 --> 00:41:54.610 align:middle line:84%
This has to do with
control over energy.

00:41:54.610 --> 00:41:57.670 align:middle line:84%
It has to do with sustainable
development, which

00:41:57.670 --> 00:41:58.820 align:middle line:90%
I believe is technocracy--

00:41:58.820 --> 00:41:59.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And money.

00:41:59.620 --> 00:42:00.810 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: And money.

00:42:00.810 --> 00:42:03.250 align:middle line:84%
And so they say,
no, enough of that.

00:42:03.250 --> 00:42:06.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, you could have any
number of choke points come up

00:42:06.100 --> 00:42:09.040 align:middle line:84%
in the next five to 10 years
around the world, where

00:42:09.040 --> 00:42:10.960 align:middle line:84%
people say, we're
not going to do that.

00:42:10.960 --> 00:42:12.790 align:middle line:84%
We're just simply
not going to do that.

00:42:12.790 --> 00:42:15.070 align:middle line:84%
One headline recently
about the yellow vests

00:42:15.070 --> 00:42:19.730 align:middle line:84%
said that they have gone
out across the country

00:42:19.730 --> 00:42:26.087 align:middle line:84%
and broken 60% of the speed
trap meters on the highways.

00:42:26.087 --> 00:42:27.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That they put in.

00:42:27.170 --> 00:42:28.380 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That they put in.

00:42:28.380 --> 00:42:31.440 align:middle line:84%
This is a technocrat
control mechanism

00:42:31.440 --> 00:42:33.360 align:middle line:84%
to read license plates
and stuff like that,

00:42:33.360 --> 00:42:34.830 align:middle line:84%
take your pictures
when you're driving.

00:42:34.830 --> 00:42:35.997 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Give you a ticket--

00:42:35.997 --> 00:42:37.457 align:middle line:90%
$100, $100.

00:42:37.457 --> 00:42:39.540 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Right, and they
send you a ticket by mail.

00:42:39.540 --> 00:42:43.590 align:middle line:84%
The yellow vest
people got an idea.

00:42:43.590 --> 00:42:45.630 align:middle line:90%
These things are spying on us.

00:42:45.630 --> 00:42:46.740 align:middle line:90%
We've had it.

00:42:46.740 --> 00:42:48.248 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
take it anymore.

00:42:48.248 --> 00:42:50.040 align:middle line:84%
They went out-- I don't
know what they did.

00:42:50.040 --> 00:42:52.110 align:middle line:84%
They took hammers, or
duct tape, or something.

00:42:52.110 --> 00:42:53.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or whatever they did.

00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:54.900 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Or whatever they did.

00:42:54.900 --> 00:42:58.050 align:middle line:90%
And they deep-sixed them.

00:42:58.050 --> 00:43:01.200 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm not necessarily
for the destruction

00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:02.550 align:middle line:90%
of private property, believe me.

00:43:02.550 --> 00:43:04.320 align:middle line:90%
But you get the point.

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:06.810 align:middle line:84%
How much do people need
to know before they

00:43:06.810 --> 00:43:07.735 align:middle line:90%
can start to resist?

00:43:07.735 --> 00:43:09.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And how far
can you push them?

00:43:09.360 --> 00:43:09.780 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That's right.

00:43:09.780 --> 00:43:12.090 align:middle line:84%
How far can you push
them before they say, no.

00:43:12.090 --> 00:43:13.710 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who pays for all this?

00:43:13.710 --> 00:43:15.860 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: We do.

00:43:15.860 --> 00:43:16.660 align:middle line:90%
We've paid for it.

00:43:16.660 --> 00:43:18.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: In taxes
and everything else.

00:43:18.130 --> 00:43:19.060 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: That's right.

00:43:19.060 --> 00:43:20.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's their plan, too?

00:43:20.650 --> 00:43:23.110 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Invariably--
well, let's face it,

00:43:23.110 --> 00:43:25.810 align:middle line:84%
cities in America today,
for a number of reasons,

00:43:25.810 --> 00:43:27.800 align:middle line:90%
are flat out of money.

00:43:27.800 --> 00:43:28.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All of them.

00:43:28.720 --> 00:43:30.310 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: Almost all of them.

00:43:30.310 --> 00:43:32.890 align:middle line:84%
Some of them are that close
to bankruptcy right now.

00:43:32.890 --> 00:43:35.170 align:middle line:90%
It's scary.

00:43:35.170 --> 00:43:39.070 align:middle line:84%
But those cities are looking
for money to do stuff.

00:43:39.070 --> 00:43:41.230 align:middle line:84%
When a Microsoft comes
along, or a Google,

00:43:41.230 --> 00:43:44.740 align:middle line:84%
or an Amazon comes along, says,
hey, we'll help you out here.

00:43:44.740 --> 00:43:47.340 align:middle line:90%


00:43:47.340 --> 00:43:49.062 align:middle line:84%
You let us install
our high technology.

00:43:49.062 --> 00:43:51.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's going to cost
you this amount of money.

00:43:51.270 --> 00:43:52.230 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: We'll give you-- yeah.

00:43:52.230 --> 00:43:53.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Give you a deal.

00:43:53.550 --> 00:43:55.758 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: You know, we'll take
a little money from you,

00:43:55.758 --> 00:43:58.623 align:middle line:84%
but you'll give us just control
over these things, and--

00:43:58.623 --> 00:44:00.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We'll get our
fees out of the things.

00:44:00.540 --> 00:44:03.020 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Yeah, we'll
charge the people.

00:44:03.020 --> 00:44:04.890 align:middle line:84%
Well, the cities
go along with it

00:44:04.890 --> 00:44:09.110 align:middle line:84%
because they figure,
nothing we can do anyway.

00:44:09.110 --> 00:44:13.920 align:middle line:84%
And they get into these unholy
relationships, most of which

00:44:13.920 --> 00:44:17.100 align:middle line:84%
I think, in the
future, will fail,

00:44:17.100 --> 00:44:19.470 align:middle line:84%
and leave the cities
doubly destroyed.

00:44:19.470 --> 00:44:21.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I think you're right.

00:44:21.390 --> 00:44:22.370 align:middle line:90%
I think you're right.

00:44:22.370 --> 00:44:25.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there will come
a time on this planet

00:44:25.520 --> 00:44:29.160 align:middle line:84%
that the people will
say, enough is enough.

00:44:29.160 --> 00:44:33.050 align:middle line:84%
Far beyond what's happening in
France, they will simply say,

00:44:33.050 --> 00:44:34.050 align:middle line:90%
enough is enough.

00:44:34.050 --> 00:44:36.060 align:middle line:90%
And then what happens?

00:44:36.060 --> 00:44:38.180 align:middle line:84%
Then we have a
worldwide-- of anarchy?

00:44:38.180 --> 00:44:39.450 align:middle line:90%
What happens?

00:44:39.450 --> 00:44:40.730 align:middle line:90%
>>WOOD: I know.

00:44:40.730 --> 00:44:42.990 align:middle line:84%
That's a difficult scenario
to kind of think through.

00:44:42.990 --> 00:44:43.970 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:44:43.970 --> 00:44:48.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And would an
army turn on its people?

00:44:48.170 --> 00:44:49.280 align:middle line:90%
I really wonder.

00:44:49.280 --> 00:44:51.380 align:middle line:90%
I spent nine years in the Navy.

00:44:51.380 --> 00:44:55.500 align:middle line:84%
If I was given an unlawful
order, I wouldn't have done it.

00:44:55.500 --> 00:44:59.460 align:middle line:84%
But what do they do when you
go to your military, your Army,

00:44:59.460 --> 00:45:03.660 align:middle line:84%
your Marines, and say, we've
got uprising in the cities.

00:45:03.660 --> 00:45:04.770 align:middle line:90%
They're looting.

00:45:04.770 --> 00:45:06.660 align:middle line:90%
They're burning buildings.

00:45:06.660 --> 00:45:08.280 align:middle line:90%
Shoot to kill.

00:45:08.280 --> 00:45:10.800 align:middle line:90%
Would they do that?

00:45:10.800 --> 00:45:13.200 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Some might,
some might not.

00:45:13.200 --> 00:45:17.190 align:middle line:84%
I think we've seen military all
over the world flip-flop back

00:45:17.190 --> 00:45:19.182 align:middle line:84%
and forth between
different forces.

00:45:19.182 --> 00:45:20.640 align:middle line:84%
Certainly in the
Mid East it's been

00:45:20.640 --> 00:45:26.910 align:middle line:84%
the case, where one group is
fighting for this group today.

00:45:26.910 --> 00:45:30.750 align:middle line:84%
Next month, they represent
a different crowd.

00:45:30.750 --> 00:45:33.720 align:middle line:84%
Same military, same uniform
same guns, but they're

00:45:33.720 --> 00:45:35.160 align:middle line:90%
serving a different master.

00:45:35.160 --> 00:45:38.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You talked about
cryptocurrencies earlier.

00:45:38.280 --> 00:45:41.490 align:middle line:84%
How prevalent do you
think they will become?

00:45:41.490 --> 00:45:43.740 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Sustainable
development and technocracy

00:45:43.740 --> 00:45:44.850 align:middle line:90%
have to be financed.

00:45:44.850 --> 00:45:47.820 align:middle line:84%
The United Nations has
written extensively on this.

00:45:47.820 --> 00:45:51.810 align:middle line:84%
They claim that
sustainable development

00:45:51.810 --> 00:45:58.860 align:middle line:84%
may take as much as $50
trillion dollars to implement

00:45:58.860 --> 00:46:01.390 align:middle line:90%
over the next 20, 25 years.

00:46:01.390 --> 00:46:03.680 align:middle line:90%
That's a lot of money.

00:46:03.680 --> 00:46:06.580 align:middle line:90%
Cities don't have that money.

00:46:06.580 --> 00:46:08.390 align:middle line:84%
Countries don't have
that kind of money.

00:46:08.390 --> 00:46:09.780 align:middle line:90%
Where's it going to come from?

00:46:09.780 --> 00:46:11.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's going
to come from us.

00:46:11.280 --> 00:46:13.540 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Well, it's going to
come from some different source.

00:46:13.540 --> 00:46:14.373 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good point.

00:46:14.373 --> 00:46:16.670 align:middle line:84%
>>WOOD: Either a different
monetary system altogether--

00:46:16.670 --> 00:46:18.670 align:middle line:84%
but something is going
to be different than what

00:46:18.670 --> 00:46:20.560 align:middle line:90%
it is today.

